text:
Tips to make your progress less painful.
1. Get a reliable food source. A large wheat farm about 15-20 blocks square. Put a fence around it so creepers won't blow up in the middle of it. You can make lot's of bread and also use the wheat to breed lots of cows.
2. Focus on mining coal and iron. You want plenty of iron for tools and most importantly, armour. A full set of iron armour will enable you to survive much better against enemies. Also when mining have a chest and furnace nearby and deposit materials regularly so that even if you die you won't lose much if you cant recover them.

Once you have your food and iron supply sorted you will find it much easier to start progressing on to other things.
